INT. CHAPEL â€“ MOMENTS LATER
The PRIEST stands under the stained-glass window, gazing out at the pew area.
The Villagers are already seated. Vani is the last one in, she takes a seat at the front.
ON the Priest, frowning.
ON Vani, listening. She casts her eyes down, ashamed.
Suddenly, a voice speaks from the darkness, echoing through the chapel. Like a judgment from a god.

Villagers look up. Startled, the Priest looks around for the source of the voice. 
BLOOD PETALS float down, cascading over the main altar and the pew area.
ON the ceiling: just darkness. Nothing there but blood petals. Where are they coming from?
Suddenly, a shadow falls over the Priest, and extends out over the pew area.
The Priest turns to see LILITH STANDING BEHIND HIM. Her wings are spread, and she is SILHOUETTED in the light from the stained-glass.

The Priest stumbles down from the main altar and backs away toward the Villagers.
He CLUTCHES A HOLY CATHEDRAL PENDANT in his hands, holding it up as if it will ward away Lilithâ€™s evil.
Lilith surveys the gathered mortals. Blood petals continue floating down, painted by beautiful light from the stained-glass.
Itâ€™s majestic, but also frightening.
Alternate line: "Search your heart for that place where you have shackled your true self."

CLOSE ON VANI. We see Lilithâ€™s silhouetted form reflected in the womanâ€™s eyes.
Lilithâ€™s voice sounds like a WHISPER in her head. Echoing. Reverberating. Almost hypnotizing. She draws out the words.
Vani rises. She gazes at Lilith, her fear melting away, replaced with something like awe, or understanding.

CLOSE ON the Priest, who is kneeling in the center of the aisle.
He looks around, concerned, at the enraptured villagers. He reaches out to them as he speaks.

CRACK! SOMEONE (we donâ€™t see who it is yet) hits the Priest across the head with a heavy CATHEDRAL CANDLESTICK.
The Priest keels over. Reveal the attacker behind him: Vani.
Her TREMBLING hand is clutching the bloody candlestick.
She stares at it, then at the Priest, almost like sheâ€™s working out in her head how it made her feel.

The Priest arches his back in pain.
REVEAL Devmir behind him, pulling a SHARP OBJECT from his back.
Vani begins to hyperventilate, maniacally breathes as she continues to murder the priest

Then the frenzy begins.
The other Villagers move in and STAB/HIT the Priest with other OBJECTS. Again and again. 
TEARS OF BLOOD stream down from the images of saintly angels in the stained-glass. The blood flows through the grooves in the glass panes.
The once brilliant gold light coming through the stained-glass slides to red, illuminating the chapel in crimson.
During the frenzied violence, Lilith passes through the aisle between the pews and stops at the doors to the church (she is still INSIDE the church).
ELIAS (wearing his hood like in the DST cinematic) emerges from the shadows next to her. They are looking at each other, not the violence O.S.

WIDE SHOT of the Villagers, silhouetted in the crimson light from the stained-glass.
They are still stabbing and beating the priest.
Blood petals cascade around them. Beautiful and unsettling.
